# Totality

**Team Members:** Dhruv

**How would you pitch your game in one line?**
Chain together ruthless slashes and blinding energy strikes as a lone warrior battling through an endless eclipse.

**What is the key mechanic(s) that make it fun?**
- High-speed dashes, wall-runs
- 2 Bit Pixel Art Style (Just black and white) which adds a touch of simplicity (but does not dimish the beauty of it)
- Many unique attacks

**How does the game actually play? (Core Game Loop)**
- Fight endless waves of enemies in a dark world 
- Every 3 waves, a shop appears with upgrades, weapons, and movement boosts
- Chain melee combos, energy slashes, and blink-dashes for fast combat
- Enemy types get harder, forcing strategy changes
- Survive as long as possible, difficulty keeps scaling
- Slight story involved

**How will you keep players engaged for 30 minutes? What's the general scope of your game (will change as you go)?**
[Describe your plan for sustaining gameplay]
- Fast, fluid combat with chainable attacks and stylish movement
- Increasing enemy variety and difficulty over time
- Shop every 3 waves for upgrades, weapons, and perks
- Dynamic lighting effects make combat visually engaging
 
